I"â<p>Nowadays, the conceptual design process of early architectural ideas has gained significant attraction. Technology plays an essential role in making this process more intuitive and efficient. Based on this premise, the <a href="http://cdp.ai.ar.tum.de/">Collaborative Design Platform</a> was developed at the Technical University of Munich as an interdisciplinary research project between the <a href="http://campar.in.tum.de/Chair/AugmentedReality">Augmented Reality</a> and <a href="https://www.loc.tum.de/lehrstuehle/architekturinformatik/">Architectural Informatics</a> chairs.</p>

<p>We strongly believe that current Augmented Reality technologies can improve significantly the user experience on the early design process stages. Augmented Reality has the power to visualize any data that we want in the real world. In particular, Microsoft HoloLens seems to be a good candidate. Therefore, the main goal of my Interdisciplinary Project is the integration of Microsoft HoloLens devices to the CDP platform using the HoloToolkit in Unity. This mean that users can see and interact with the virtual scene directly on top of the projection surface.</p>

